  "summary": "game behaves as if the reducedDebugInfo gamerule was set to true even when it s false",
  "environment_raw": null,
  "description": "Most options in the F3 F5 screen are greyed out and say Not visible when debug info is reduced when I hover over the text. n nF3 B and F3 G also don t work regardless of the gamerule. n n",
  "Steps to Reproduce": "1. Launch Minecraft and create a new world in Creative mode with default settings.\n2. Open the chat window and enter the command `/gamerule reducedDebugInfo false` to ensure the gamerule is set to false.\n3. Press the F3 key to open the debug screen.\n4. Observe that most options in the debug screen (F3 + F5) are still greyed out and display \"Not visible\" when hovered over.\n5. Press F3 + B to check if entity hitboxes are displayed; note that they do not appear.\n6. Press F3 + G to check if chunk boundaries are displayed; confirm that they do not appear.\n7. Attempt to use the F3 + C command to copy coordinates and verify that it does not function as expected.\n8. Repeat the previous steps to confirm that the issue persists throughout multiple attempts.",
  "Environment": "Minecraft Java Edition Version 25w31a (snapshot)",
  "Observed Behavior": "When the `reducedDebugInfo` gamerule is set to false, the debug screen (activated by pressing F3) still displays limited information as if the gamerule were true. Specifically, most options in the F3 and F5 debug screens are greyed out and indicate \"Not visible\" when hovered over. This includes critical toggles such as F3 + B (to show entity hitboxes) and F3 + G (to display chunk boundaries), which do not function as expected regardless of the gamerule setting. Additionally, the F3 + C command, typically used to copy coordinates, is also inoperative. This behavior is inconsistent with the intended functionality of the `reducedDebugInfo` gamerule, which should allow full access to debug information when set to false. \n\nSteps to reproduce this issue:\n1. Set the `reducedDebugInfo` gamerule to false using the command `/gamerule reducedDebugInfo false`.\n2. Press F3 to open the debug screen.\n3. Observe that many options are still greyed out and non-functional, contrary to the expected behavior when the gamerule is false. \n4. Attempt to use F3 + B and F3 + G, noting that they do not activate. \n\nThis bug disrupts the expected functionality of the debug information display, impacting players who rely on these features for gameplay analysis and troubleshooting.",
  "Expected Behavior": "When the reducedDebugInfo gamerule is set to false, the debug screen should display all relevant information without any options greyed out. Specifically, pressing F3 should allow access to the full range of debug options, including F3 + B (to show entity hitboxes) and F3 + G (to show chunk boundaries), without any restrictions. Additionally, the F3 + C and F3 + I commands should function normally, allowing players to copy coordinates and block/entity data, respectively. The game should not exhibit any limitations on the debug information displayed, ensuring that all features are accessible as intended by Minecraft's design.",
